<BaseLayout title="About" {description}><header class="simple-hero"><div class="container"><span class="eyebrow">About Grass Whisperer</span><h1>Better lawns through better observation.</h1><p>This site exists to replace product-first lawn advice with clear explanations of how grass, soil, water and seasons work together.</p></div></header><section><div class="container about-grid"><aside>Independent guidance for ordinary British gardens.</aside><div><h2>Our approach</h2><p>Grass Whisperer helps home gardeners understand the cause before choosing a treatment. The guides favour measured interventions, responsible water use and techniques that strengthen the lawn over time.</p><p>Advice is written for the UK climate, but local soil, shade, rainfall and restrictions always matter. Product labels and current local guidance take priority where they are more specific.</p><h2>Editorial standards</h2><p>We separate the role of a material from the promise on its packaging, explain limitations, and avoid pretending there is one perfect schedule for every lawn. Content is reviewed and dated so readers can judge how current it is.</p><p class="disclaimer"><strong>Important:</strong> This website provides general gardening information, not site-specific professional advice. Investigate suspected subsidence, drainage failures, utilities, chemical exposure or serious plant disease with a suitably qualified professional. Always follow product labels and local water-use rules.</p></div></div></section></BaseLayout>
